# Live-only packages (not copied to the installed system).
# Keep minimal: the installer is the only "app" the live image needs.

# Seat management for the LIVE environment. Per project decision the live ISO
# uses seatd (lightweight) for seat/device access during boot. The installed
# system's seat backend is chosen separately by the user in the installer.
seatd
seatd-dinit

# Wi-Fi testing in a VM (scripts/wifi-test.sh): hostapd fakes an access
